      "mediumHeading": "Sharding vs Partitioning"
    },
    {
      "smallHeading": "1. Meaning"
    },
    {
      "table": {
        "headers": [
          "Sharding",
          "Partitioning"
        ],
        "rows": [
          [
            "Sharding is the process of dividing data across multiple databases or servers.\nEach shard is stored on a different machine.",
            "Partitioning is the process of dividing data within a single database.\nAll partitions stay on the same server."
